{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fixedSize","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that fixes this view at its ideal size.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"During the layout of the view hierarchy, each view proposes a size to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"each child view it contains. If the child view doesn’t need a fixed size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can accept and conform to the size offered by the parent.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" view placed in an explicitly sized frame wraps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and truncates its string to remain within its parent’s bounds:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"text":" modifier can be used to create a view that maintains","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ideal size","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" of its children both dimensions:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .fixedSize()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"may not be the effect you want.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can think of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" as the creation of a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"counter proposal"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view, and the specific effects of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" depends on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"particular view and how you have configured it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertical dimensions, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/roundedrectangle\/fixedsize()"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/RoundedRectangle"]]},"a